node.text:
Join Dior global ambassador @YaraShahidi as she takes a private tour of the #DiorDesignerofDreams exhibition at the @BrooklynMuseum in the company of curator Florence Müller. The actress and activist identifies 'The Dior Legacy', the room showcasing the work of Monsieur Dior's successors, as her favorite. She also has the honor of discovering that a tarot-inspired #DiorCouture Spring-Summer 2019 outfit by @MariaGraziaChiuri she had previously worn had also made the cut to be included among the more than 200 couture creations on display.
© Photo: @LelanieF

node.title: Yara Shahidi's private tour of 'Christian Dior: Designer of Dreams'

node.text: Acquire an insightful understanding of how the landmark #DiorDesignerofDreams exhibition was conceived at the @BrooklynMuseum in New York. Curators Florence Müller and @Matthew_Yokobosky along with scenographer Nathalie Crinière (@Agence_NC_Nathalie_Criniere) reveal the challenges and opportunities posed by the unique space, how the host city altered the narrative, and how art and couture forged a symbiotic alliance.

node.title: Bringing 'Christian Dior: Designer of Dreams' to life

Curator Florence Müller shares insights into Christian Dior’s relationship with New York as she showcases designs featured in the #DiorDesignerofDreams exhibition at the @BrooklynMuseum until February 20, 2022. Invited to the United States by Neiman Marcus to receive the department store’s prestigious fashion award mere months after his earth-shattering debut with the New Look, for the founding couturier his first impressions of New York were equally astonishing. Struck by its architecture, culture and energy, he would open a subsidiary of his couture house on Fifth Avenue the following year, with creations specially designed for the American market.
© Photo: @HereandNowAgency

Join @PSG players as they get fitted for the formalwear part of their new wardrobe designed by @MrKimJones,
in a partnership that sees Dior become the football team’s official tailor for the next two seasons. The outfits
comprise a cashmere coat, single-breasted jacket, shirt and pants, along with a pair of black leather ‘Dior
Timeless’ cap-toe derbies whose insoles are silver-tone embossed with each player’s number. A tie woven with a ‘Paris Saint-Germain’ logo, cashmere scarf and reversible black and navy belt complete the looks.
#PSGxDior
© @MelindaTriana

node.text: Serious style hits the slopes with the #DiorAlps capsule from #DiorAW21 by @MariaGraziaChiuri, shot here by @EstelleHanania for #DiorMagazine 35. Combining cutting-edge activewear with bold fashion statements, pompom-trimmed ski hats and beanie meet unmistakable 'Dior Oblique' and 'Mizza' leopard motifs, as ski suits and separates come accessorized with 'DiorAlps Low Boots' and pop with tricolor examples of Monsieur Dior’s lucky star. The line is now available in boutiques and online.

node.text: Acquire an insightful understanding of how the landmark #DiorDesignerofDreams exhibition was conceived at the @BrooklynMuseum in New York. Curators Florence Müller and @Matthew_Yokobosky along with scenographer Nathalie Crinière (@Agence_NC_Nathalie_Criniere) reveal the challenges and opportunities posed by the unique space, how the host city altered the narrative, and how art and couture forged a symbiotic alliance.

node.text:
Wowing visitors to the #DiorDesignerofDreams exhibition with an intense impression of thrilling wonder, the central atrium of the Beaux-Arts Court at the @BrooklynMuseum has been reimagined by scenographer Nathalie Crinière (@Agence_NC_Nathalie_Criniere) for the occasion as an enchanted garden with a sky constellated by stars, an echo of Christian Dior's lucky star, the chance discovery of which represents the symbolic beginning to the House’s incomparable history relayed here in glorious detail until February 20, 2022.

node.text:
The profusion of gorgeous gowns offers a welcome sensory overload at the #DiorDesignerofDreams exhibition currently running at the @BrooklynMuseum. The most exquisite eveningwear - including dazzling looks worn by a host of famous actresses - ensures a breathtaking discovery at every turn. With a section titled 'The Dior Legacy', visitors can discover how Christian Dior's successors, from Yves Saint Laurent to @MariaGraziaChiuri, have interpreted and transformed his aesthetics and codes. Another illuminating display charts the presence of Dior on the covers of fashion magazines across the past seven-plus decades.
© @HereandNowAgency

node.text:
Curator Florence Müller shares insights into Christian Dior’s relationship with New York as she showcases designs featured in the #DiorDesignerofDreams exhibition at the @BrooklynMuseum until February 20, 2022. Invited to the United States by Neiman Marcus to receive the department store’s prestigious fashion award mere months after his earth-shattering debut with the New Look, for the founding couturier his first impressions of New York were equally astonishing. Struck by its architecture, culture and energy, he would open a subsidiary of his couture house on Fifth Avenue the following year, with creations specially designed for the American market.
© Photo: @HereandNowAgency
